Kitui Governor Julius Malombe has urged residents from the county living in Garissa town to register as voters there and exercise their constitutional right of electing their leaders.&ldquo;You do not have to go home and register to vote for Malombe or [David] Musila in Kitui. Remain here and exercise your rights to participate in elections,&rdquo; Malombe said at a Garissa hotel on Saturday.He accompanied Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka during a meeting with Kambas living in the town. They were hosted by Garissa Governor Nathif Jama.Malombe urged the Kambas to live harmoniously with the indigenous people and avoid conflict. Two weeks ago, an audio clip was circulated on the internet, inciting Garissa residents not to allow Kambas register as voters.The voice was said to be that of Garissa Township MP Aden Duale, which he denies.